## Project Scope
This educational gamification ecosystem creates the foundation for the "Minime Universe" - an expandable platform of educational games centered around personalized 3D avatars. The core Sangsom Mini-Me application serves as the hub where students care for their digital selves while academic achievements from both homework completion and educational side games contribute to character development and resource accumulation.

### Long-term Vision
- **Expandable Universe:** Platform designed to accommodate multiple educational games
- **Cross-Game Integration:** Seamless resource and progress sharing between applications  
- **Educational Impact:** Direct correlation between academic performance and gaming rewards
- **Scalable Infrastructure:** Multi-user, multi-account system capable of serving entire schools
- **Administrative Control:** Teacher and administrator tools for monitoring and customization

### First Implementation - Leandi Test Model
The initial development phase focuses on creating and testing the core systems using "Leandi" as the prototype model, establishing the foundational technology and user experience that will scale to serve multiple students across the educational system.
















